<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf69710a7-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12307"><num value="12307">§ 12307.</num><heading> Regulations on numbering and fees</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The authority issuing a number under this chapter may prescribe regulations and establish fees to carry out the intent of this chapter. The fees shall apply equally to residents and nonresidents of the State. A State issuing authority may impose only conditions for vessel numbering that are—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf69710a8-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12307/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> prescribed by this chapter or regulations of the Secretary about the standard numbering system; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf69710a9-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12307/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> related to proof of payment of State or local taxes.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf69710aa-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/591">97 Stat. 591</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
